1
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:27,360
Your Majesty.

2
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:29,362
Prince Iksang has arrived.

3
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,366
Is his son with him as well?

4
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,702
Yes, Your Majesty.

5
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:39,998
How is Prince Yeongan?

6
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:44,753
His condition has not improved,
so he will not be able to attend.

7
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:54,763
- You may leave.
- Yes, Your Majesty.

8
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:02,604
It seems that man, Gu-cheon, has failed.

9
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,150
People say

10
00:01:08,151 --> 00:01:11,446
I took the throne because of a spirit.

11
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:13,615
Yet now they mock me,

12
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,661
saying my throne will be shaken by it.

13
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:23,124
Which do you think is true?

14
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,810
We will know when we get there.

15
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:49,818
The royal affines and the kin officials.

16
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:52,779
Perform four ceremonial bows.

17
00:01:58,409 --> 00:02:00,578
Bow.

18
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,373
Rise.

19
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:05,750
Bow.

20
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,586
Rise.

21
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:11,339
Bow.

22
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,925
Rise.

23
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:25,979
Next, the Crown Prince should offer wine,

24
00:02:26,062 --> 00:02:29,065
praying for Your Majesty's longevity
and good health.

25
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,193
However, the seat is vacant.

26
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:35,029
- Perhaps this should be omitted--
- No.

27
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:38,783
This old body of mine

28
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:43,037
may not last
until another birthday banquet.

29
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:46,749
What do you think, Your Majesty?

30
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,381
As you wish, Mother.

31
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:07,687
The eldest son of Prince Iksang,
step forward!

32
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:10,356
Prince Iksang, congratulations.

33
00:03:40,136 --> 00:03:42,639
This is the cup of wine
offered by Prince Inha.

34
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:46,976
I pray for Your Majesty's longevity
and good health.

35
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,331
What is happening?

36
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,918
How did the door…

37
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,715
- Something is here.
- Your Majesty.

38
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:28,786
<i>Yes.</i>

39
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,874
<i>I knew you would return to me</i>
<i>in resentment</i>

40
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:36,961
<i>once I had tormented you.</i>

41
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,505
<i>Now,</i>

42
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,050
<i>what will you do?</i>

43
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:03,946
Gu-cheon!

44
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,251
Come to your senses!

45
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:22,256
Do you truly wish to kill someone
and become an ak-gwi?

46
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:28,888
You said becoming an ak-gwi after death

47
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:32,266
was the thing you feared the most.

48
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:39,315
Gu-cheon!

49
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:42,568
You are not to blame
for the death of your mother.

50
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:51,035
That gwi-mae has taken hold of you.

51
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,080
If you still cannot trust me,

52
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:56,999
I will uncover the truth.

53
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,210
Once I leave the palace,

54
00:06:59,293 --> 00:07:01,879
I will find your mother's soul
and reveal the truth.

55
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:12,014
So let us

56
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:15,393
make it out of the palace alive.

57
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:05,026
THE EAST PALACE

58
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:22,001
- Prince Inha!
- Prince Inha!

59
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:24,712
What is wrong with him?
What is happening to him?

60
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:26,422
- All of a sudden…
- Wake up!

61
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:28,132
Summon the physician!

62
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,426
- Send for the physician!
- Summon the physician!

63
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:31,886
Your Majesty.

64
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,559
The child is flawed.

65
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:46,025
This must be disappointing for you,
Mother.

66
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,529
In such a frail state,

67
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:54,158
how could he ever withstand
the energy of the palace?

68
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:02,041
You would need to become
a better judge of character.

69
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:05,503
Continue the banquet.

70
00:09:06,003 --> 00:09:08,172
Let the music continue!

71
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:11,342
Attend to Prince Inha at once!

72
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,548
No.

73
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:02,852
Princess.

74
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:04,937
Princess!

75
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,544
Have you lost your mind?

76
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,380
I told you never to set foot in there.

77
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:33,883
You never listen to me.

78
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:37,261
I saved you, yet you reproach me.

79
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:40,222
You could have died and become a spirit.

80
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:43,768
- Was I supposed to just stand by?
- Never do that again.

81
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:46,103
Whether I become a spirit
or a wandering soul.

82
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:50,566
I never want to see anyone die
because of me again.

83
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,042
If you insist,

84
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,795
I will never do it again.

85
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:13,255
I cannot

86
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:17,093
bring myself to go in there again either.

87
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:19,428
I was terrified.

88
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:24,600
It must have been

89
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:28,270
a difficult time for you.

90
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,445
No such thing as spirits.

91
00:12:19,029 --> 00:12:20,197
Mother.

92
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,408
Spirits do not exist.

93
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,287
Spirits do not exist.

94
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:28,789
Mother?

95
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:33,252
It is your father who is the spirit.

96
00:12:58,569 --> 00:12:59,403
Are you all right?

97
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:06,494
What are you doing there?

98
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:08,204
How is your fever?

99
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:12,792
Why open the door without asking?

100
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:17,505
You still have that temper.

101
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:26,639
Miss Saeng-gang!

102
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:28,974
Are you up?

103
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,727
What is going on?

104
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:37,942
I thought Gu-cheon was dead,
yet he is walking around alive.

105
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:42,863
I thought you were fine, but you slept
for three days and nights as if dead.

106
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:45,157
- I slept for three days?
- Yes.

107
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:46,826
Have these first.

108
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:49,453
I begged the female physician
for this herbal medicine

109
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:51,872
and snuck these rice cakes
from Saenggwabang.

110
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:54,250
You have not eaten at all for three days.

111
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:56,961
Here. Please eat.

112
00:13:58,212 --> 00:13:59,296
Thank you.

113
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:10,933
But why did you bring so many rice cakes?

114
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:16,063
Gu-cheon has not eaten for three days
either, so I brought his share.

115
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:17,731
But he just left.

116
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:19,692
Looks like he has no luck with food.

117
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:21,735
Is he not even hungry?

118
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:39,587
After three days without food,
it tastes even better.

119
00:14:40,754 --> 00:14:41,922
Are you not going to eat?

120
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:46,635
I have no appetite.

121
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:48,345
You eat it all.

122
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,267
You should eat too.

123
00:14:54,935 --> 00:14:59,356
You need to eat to work. Do not forget
what I found in the royal guard's place.

124
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:02,443
I will handle that myself,

125
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:04,987
so you need not concern yourself,
Your Highness.

126
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,906
"Your Highness"?

127
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:11,076
Why? What?

128
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:15,956
You seem to have changed.

129
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:31,805
By the way, where is what you found
at the royal guard's residence?

130
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:37,227
The Most Favored Lady of the Court
made this for the child she was carrying.

131
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:43,901
Do you think this could ease
her resentment?

132
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:46,946
It may be possible,

133
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,406
but it will take a lot of preparation.

134
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,867
She is no ordinary spirit.

135
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,788
She is a won-gwi
and has killed for 30 years.

136
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:01,210
Oh, right. Where did you get
that lightning-struck jujube wood?

137
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:05,631
Oh. A jujube tree inside the palace
was struck by lightning.

138
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,634
Did it help at all?

139
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:12,054
It was a great help.

140
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:13,722
And it will continue to be.

141
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:15,432
Then

142
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:18,519
you could at least say thank you.

143
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:21,146
I believe I have helped you in many ways.

144
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:25,526
Can you not see that kind of showing off
kills all my gratitude?

145
00:16:25,609 --> 00:16:27,528
How is that showing off?

146
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:29,905
I deserve a word of thanks.

147
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,574
I nearly died
handling your family's affairs.

148
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,034
A word of thanks? Ridiculous.

149
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:36,412
Do you want recognition that badly?

150
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:39,206
- Good grief.
- Good heavens.

151
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:42,960
Forget it.

152
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:46,630
You do not need to thank me.

153
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:48,716
Just say thank you to Ggeomeoksali.

154
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:52,720
It saved you from the gwi-mae in the well.

155
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:54,888
Did it?

156
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:57,433
No wonder I have not seen it
these past few days.

157
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,768
It fell into the well
while fighting the gwi-mae.

158
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:01,395
Oh dear.

159
00:17:01,937 --> 00:17:03,105
Good riddance.

160
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:07,943
How heartless of you!

161
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:11,655
I do not do foolish things
like growing attached to gwi-mae.

162
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:14,867
Let us just focus
on how to banish the pond spirit.

163
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:27,713
What is wrong?

164
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:29,506
Well…

165
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:38,766
<i>when I crossed over to the other side,</i>
<i>I came face-to-face with the pond spirit.</i>

166
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:44,188
<i>It clawed at my back</i>
<i>and drained my energy,</i>

167
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:48,776
<i>but you pulled the rope just in time,</i>
<i>and I was freed from it.</i>

168
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:53,363
<i>"Clawed"?</i>

169
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,042
What is the matter?

170
00:18:12,424 --> 00:18:14,760
The pond spirit that consumed your soul…

171
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,598
must be regaining its power.

172
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,601
<i>The curse that faltered for a moment</i>

173
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:24,645
<i>will grow stronger again.</i>

174
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:26,605
Your Majesty.

175
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,483
The physician attending
Prince Yeongan says

176
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:32,569
you must prepare yourself for the worst.

177
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:46,708
Why…

178
00:18:57,344 --> 00:19:01,682
I am not sure if we should
fight the pond spirit on impulse.

179
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:06,728
Prince Yeongan
will not make it through the night.

180
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:10,315
The lingering curse
must have pushed his body to the limit.

181
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,734
We have no time to waste.

182
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:21,743
Can you not hear it?

183
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,203
That sound?

184
00:19:39,052 --> 00:19:40,345
Be careful.

185
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:44,725
I will not save someone
who does not even thank me.

186
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:46,518
Still holding onto it?

187
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:28,977
My baby…

188
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:48,372
<i>Can you shoot arrows?</i>

189
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:51,667
<i>Everyone tried to stop me</i>
<i>because I am a princess, but I insisted.</i>

190
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,335
<i>I learned it from my father.</i>

191
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,879
<i>So you have been odd</i>
<i>since you were little.</i>

192
00:20:56,546 --> 00:20:59,091
<i>The baby's shirt</i>
<i>the Most Favored Lady of the Court made.</i>

193
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:01,009
<i>Take a thread stained with my blood.</i>

194
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:04,304
<i>Wrap this thread around an arrow.</i>
<i>Strike the spirit.</i>

195
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:06,556
<i>It will weaken its resentment.</i>

196
00:21:07,724 --> 00:21:08,558
Here.

197
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:13,146
<i>When the baby stops crying,</i>

198
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:15,065
<i>shoot the arrow.</i>

199
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:19,403
<i>Her resentment over false accusation</i>

200
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:22,864
<i>and the grief of losing her child</i>
<i>need to be eased.</i>

201
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:04,489
Killing those of royal blood
will not bring your baby back.

202
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:07,784
So let go of your resentment
and pass on to the afterlife.

203
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:12,581
Free yourself from this hellish palace!

204
00:22:48,658 --> 00:22:49,993
Your Majesty.

205
00:22:50,077 --> 00:22:51,661
Prince Yeongan has awakened.

206
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:53,121
What?

207
00:22:55,374 --> 00:22:57,584
Do you mean he is improving?

208
00:22:57,667 --> 00:23:01,088
Not merely improving, but a full recovery.

209
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:05,717
<i>The feng shui master His Majesty brought</i>
<i>seems to have banished the pond spirit.</i>

210
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:10,931
Your Majesty.

211
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:19,564
Father.

212
00:23:25,278 --> 00:23:26,321
Yes.

213
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:39,334
<i>He ended the curse</i>
<i>that has endured for 30 years?</i>

214
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:44,923
But…

215
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:49,636
that feng shui master.

216
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:53,432
How did he drive off the pond spirit?

217
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:56,977
I am not sure, Your Majesty.

218
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:59,563
While banishing the pond spirit,

219
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:03,233
he must have learned its true identity.

220
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,611
That man knows the secret.

221
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:09,865
He knows how that lowly maidservant
became a won-gwi.

222
00:24:10,991 --> 00:24:13,952
We must silence him.

223
00:24:21,668 --> 00:24:24,337
<i>The pond spirit has been banished.</i>

224
00:24:26,256 --> 00:24:27,340
Yes.

225
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:30,886
So it seems.

226
00:24:31,386 --> 00:24:33,472
Since I carried out your orders,

227
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:36,016
I deserve a reward, do I not?

228
00:24:44,357 --> 00:24:45,567
Before that…

229
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:04,836
<i>Father,</i>

230
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:07,422
the palace frightens me.

231
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:08,673
Frightens you?

232
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:11,593
Who would dare frighten a princess?

233
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:15,555
I keep hearing strange sounds.

234
00:25:17,891 --> 00:25:19,476
Saeng-gang, come here.

235
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:25,232
Here. Carry this with you.

236
00:25:25,315 --> 00:25:27,150
If you do so,

237
00:25:28,235 --> 00:25:30,737
this bell will ward off
those strange sounds.

238
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:40,872
Thanks to you, he lived.

239
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:43,416
Thank you.

240
00:25:48,797 --> 00:25:51,675
I did not do this
to be praised like a child.

241
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:55,554
Very well.

242
00:25:57,138 --> 00:26:00,433
Then what reward do you desire?

243
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:03,436
First, allow Gu-cheon to leave the palace.

244
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,565
Of course I will.

245
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:07,983
Without harming him.

246
00:26:08,858 --> 00:26:11,736
That is my humble request.

247
00:26:21,329 --> 00:26:23,623
Why are you not packing your things?

248
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:29,004
I have nothing on me. All I need
is the lightning-struck jujube wood.

249
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:36,511
You are leaving the palace,
yet you do not look happy.

250
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:38,597
It is just…

251
00:26:41,391 --> 00:26:42,726
something feels off.

252
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,062
What do you mean?

253
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:50,108
Has Prince Yeongan truly recovered?
Is he completely well?

254
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:52,235
That is what I was told.

255
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,655
And how is your wound?

256
00:26:56,823 --> 00:26:58,742
The pain is gone.

257
00:27:00,076 --> 00:27:01,328
What is it?

258
00:27:03,079 --> 00:27:05,874
It was not a spirit
that could be banished so easily.

259
00:27:06,416 --> 00:27:09,961
A won-gwi that had killed the princes
of the East Palace for 30 years.

260
00:27:10,503 --> 00:27:13,381
Four sons of the late King
and three sons of the present King.

261
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:16,426
For a won-gwi that killed seven,

262
00:27:17,594 --> 00:27:20,055
it was too weak.

263
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:22,307
Are you sure…

264
00:27:24,559 --> 00:27:27,312
those princes were killed
by the pond spirit?

265
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:29,981
If it was not the pond spirit,

266
00:27:30,815 --> 00:27:31,775
then what was it?

267
00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:36,863
I suppose…

268
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:40,492
I thought it would be hard enough
to put my life at risk.

269
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:45,080
But now that it is easily resolved,
all sorts of thoughts come to mind.

270
00:27:45,872 --> 00:27:49,501
Good heavens, I must be out of my mind.
Completely out of my mind.

271
00:27:50,794 --> 00:27:54,089
So once you leave the palace,
will you return to the temple?

272
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:55,382
Do you think I am mad?

273
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:58,718
I am still thinking about where to go.

274
00:28:01,262 --> 00:28:02,389
And what will you do?

275
00:28:02,889 --> 00:28:04,724
Did you find who did it to your mother?

276
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:10,355
It can only be that person.

277
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:36,715
You are the daughter
of the banished Third Senior Consort Han.

278
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:39,509
What brings you to the palace, Princess?

279
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:44,305
I have brought a gift to celebrate
the 70th birthday of Your Majesty.

280
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:47,934
It is quite modest compared to the others.

281
00:28:48,435 --> 00:28:51,563
You came all this way for nothing.

282
00:28:53,022 --> 00:28:56,234
I never permitted you to enter the palace.

283
00:28:56,317 --> 00:28:58,737
Father granted permission.

284
00:28:58,820 --> 00:28:59,696
What did you say?

285
00:28:59,779 --> 00:29:01,948
His Majesty did so without consulting me?

286
00:29:02,449 --> 00:29:05,076
Even when your mother was banished
for her crime?

287
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,495
You mean the court lady incident
in the salt store?

288
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:10,331
You framed my mother
and cast her out to cover it up.

289
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:12,500
You must have feared

290
00:29:12,584 --> 00:29:15,670
the Most Favored Lady of the Court's death
would come to light.

291
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:19,924
The shameful secret of Your Majesty,
tied to the pond spirit.

292
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:30,518
You burst in
and speak nothing but nonsense.

293
00:29:31,227 --> 00:29:35,857
Your mother was banished
for burying a cursed object.

294
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:39,652
- She denied her guilt to the very end--
- Is that why you killed my mother?

295
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:45,658
As she kept pleading with Father
for her life,

296
00:29:46,409 --> 00:29:48,953
did you fear that your sin,
buried in the salt storehouse,

297
00:29:50,538 --> 00:29:52,707
the serpent's cast skin, would be exposed?

298
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:56,836
Is it your upbringing outside the palace,
or your baseborn mother?

299
00:29:58,588 --> 00:30:00,632
You have truly lost your mind.

300
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:03,593
How dare you make
such absurd accusations against me!

301
00:30:06,554 --> 00:30:07,639
Open the gift.

302
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,609
I made the same sweets

303
00:30:20,109 --> 00:30:22,654
my mother received from the palace
the day before she died.

304
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:33,790
<i>Not only the taste</i>
<i>but also the ingredients are the same.</i>

305
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:35,667
Please try some.

306
00:30:58,898 --> 00:31:02,193
Who on earth told you such lies?

307
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:07,073
I had no part in the deaths of your mother
and the Most Favored Lady of the Court.

308
00:31:07,574 --> 00:31:10,535
How could you possibly know
of events from…

309
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,165
Is that what you heard from Gu-cheon,
that feng shui master?

310
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:21,546
I should have taught that bastard sooner

311
00:31:21,629 --> 00:31:25,800
what becomes of those
who lie in the palace.

312
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:28,511
It means death.

313
00:31:36,269 --> 00:31:39,606
Now tell me what you have learned
about the pond spirit.

314
00:31:39,689 --> 00:31:40,899
The pond spirit?

315
00:31:41,482 --> 00:31:42,567
What is that?

316
00:31:42,650 --> 00:31:46,362
Do you mean your grandfather
who drowned while bathing in the summer?

317
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,200
Throw him into a chest.

318
00:31:58,666 --> 00:32:04,047
<i>In this austere palace,</i>
<i>only death awaits those who lie.</i>

319
00:32:04,130 --> 00:32:05,757
Just like your mother.

320
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:09,677
I will return

321
00:32:10,803 --> 00:32:12,013
those very words to you.

322
00:32:18,895 --> 00:32:22,106
This is the baby's first shirt
the Most Favored Lady of the Court made.

323
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:24,484
You gave this to the royal guard

324
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:26,778
and made him falsely claim
the child was his.

325
00:32:28,279 --> 00:32:33,493
- What are you--
- The Most Favored Lady of the Court.

326
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:37,330
You framed her and wiped out
the late King's bloodline.

327
00:32:38,331 --> 00:32:40,166
The late King's bloodline?

328
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:43,920
That lowly maidservant
who took up with a mere royal guard?

329
00:32:44,003 --> 00:32:45,463
Why did you go that far?

330
00:32:46,339 --> 00:32:48,883
Unlike the other concubines
favored by the King,

331
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:51,803
you framed and killed
the Most Favored Lady of the Court. Why?

332
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:56,849
Out of jealousy?

333
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:04,107
Jealousy?

334
00:33:11,114 --> 00:33:13,074
Did you say jealousy?

335
00:33:13,157 --> 00:33:17,245
Toward that lowborn wench?

336
00:33:19,872 --> 00:33:22,667
She once lived as a household slave
of my family.

337
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:26,629
And I was the one who allowed her
into the palace as a maidservant.

338
00:33:26,713 --> 00:33:27,922
And I was jealous of her?

339
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:30,008
Nonsense!

340
00:33:35,263 --> 00:33:40,768
I come from a long line of nobles!

341
00:33:41,394 --> 00:33:43,604
But for years,

342
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:49,652
I was scorned by the late King
for bearing no child.

343
00:33:49,736 --> 00:33:54,240
Yet that lowly slave won
His Majesty's favor and bore him a child!

344
00:33:55,324 --> 00:33:57,493
I could not accept it.

345
00:33:57,994 --> 00:34:02,415
I could accept concubines
from noble households and their children.

346
00:34:03,374 --> 00:34:06,544
Yet the bloodline
carried by that lowborn woman

347
00:34:06,627 --> 00:34:11,716
had to be cut off, by any means necessary.

348
00:34:13,968 --> 00:34:16,137
Is that why you falsely accused her?

349
00:34:16,637 --> 00:34:18,056
That is right!

350
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:21,100
I had that wretch tortured

351
00:34:21,934 --> 00:34:26,481
and destroyed that filthy bloodline
in her womb!

352
00:34:32,612 --> 00:34:33,529
Your Majesty!

353
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:40,745
I heard you clearly.

354
00:34:41,746 --> 00:34:45,208
Killing the Most Favored Lady of the Court
and the child of the late King.

355
00:34:46,292 --> 00:34:47,585
You confessed to it.

356
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:51,297
What?

357
00:34:51,798 --> 00:34:54,884
I will make this public
before Father and the ministers.

358
00:34:56,803 --> 00:34:58,721
And you stated clearly earlier

359
00:34:58,805 --> 00:35:01,974
that only death awaits those who lie.

360
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:08,648
Then tell me, Your Majesty.
What would death mean to you?

361
00:35:09,148 --> 00:35:12,276
It would mean losing the palace,
which is everything to you.

362
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:19,450
All that power you have enjoyed
and the home you have lived in.

363
00:35:20,743 --> 00:35:21,911
I will take it all away.

364
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:29,627
And how would you…

365
00:35:30,211 --> 00:35:34,132
Who would ever believe
someone of such low birth,

366
00:35:34,215 --> 00:35:37,927
banished from the palace?

367
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:41,430
I know that well.

368
00:35:43,015 --> 00:35:47,019
Who would listen
to a mere princess like me?

369
00:35:56,487 --> 00:36:00,658
Your voice was loud enough
for everyone to hear.

370
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:03,244
Now,

371
00:36:05,037 --> 00:36:06,497
will you kill these people

372
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:10,293
and bury them like the court ladies
in the salt storehouse?

373
00:36:13,212 --> 00:36:15,798
You will need a lot of jars
for their bones.

374
00:36:17,216 --> 00:36:18,050
Let us go.

375
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:37,445
Your Majesty!

376
00:36:43,534 --> 00:36:45,494
I cannot look away for even a moment.

377
00:36:45,995 --> 00:36:47,914
Why are you lying there all beaten up?

378
00:36:59,383 --> 00:37:01,552
What trouble did you cause

379
00:37:02,511 --> 00:37:04,805
that Her Majesty the Queen Dowager
wants you dead?

380
00:37:06,515 --> 00:37:08,559
I thought it was His Majesty
who ordered this.

381
00:37:09,393 --> 00:37:12,188
To see whether I could keep a secret.

382
00:37:14,273 --> 00:37:15,608
Since you are so certain,

383
00:37:16,317 --> 00:37:18,694
denying it would be pointless.

384
00:37:22,531 --> 00:37:24,492
Then why do you spare me?

385
00:37:26,827 --> 00:37:29,205
The Princess pleaded earnestly
with His Majesty

386
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:33,334
to let you leave the palace unharmed.

387
00:37:34,502 --> 00:37:37,046
She must have known this would happen.

388
00:37:45,137 --> 00:37:46,764
Your pass to leave the palace.

389
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:51,185
And this is your compensation.

390
00:37:53,479 --> 00:37:55,064
Watch your mouth.

391
00:37:55,564 --> 00:37:58,150
All eight provinces of Joseon
are in His Majesty's grasp.

392
00:38:23,092 --> 00:38:25,845
They do not let me go so easily.

393
00:38:28,431 --> 00:38:30,224
Still, it is over now.

394
00:39:06,761 --> 00:39:07,970
I saw nothing.

395
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:10,723
I did not see anything. Nothing at all.

396
00:39:18,564 --> 00:39:19,398
For heaven's sake.

397
00:39:42,171 --> 00:39:44,382
I have repaid my debt to you
for saving me.

398
00:39:46,092 --> 00:39:47,134
Take care.

399
00:40:09,532 --> 00:40:13,702
I will give you some of my Yang energy.
Just enough for you to recover.

400
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:24,839
Let go! That is enough, damn it!

401
00:40:25,339 --> 00:40:26,173
Enough!

402
00:40:52,867 --> 00:40:54,410
You do not look well.

403
00:40:55,661 --> 00:40:56,787
Are you ill?

404
00:40:58,080 --> 00:41:01,500
I suppose working alongside Gu-cheon
has worn me out.

405
00:41:03,252 --> 00:41:07,173
And last night, you caused quite a scene
at the Queen Dowager's residence,

406
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:09,300
so it is only natural.

407
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:13,179
What will you do about the Queen Dowager?

408
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:16,891
Is that why you came to see me
this early in the morning?

409
00:41:17,391 --> 00:41:18,350
No.

410
00:41:18,434 --> 00:41:22,480
I wanted to make sure
that Gu-cheon left the palace safely.

411
00:41:26,567 --> 00:41:28,527
You worry about him too much.

412
00:41:29,737 --> 00:41:31,447
He must have left the palace.

413
00:41:32,072 --> 00:41:34,283
He should be on his way by now.

414
00:41:34,366 --> 00:41:36,118
And he saved my son.

415
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:41,332
I have no intention of harming

416
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:44,710
the one who saved my child.

417
00:41:46,629 --> 00:41:48,005
Do not worry.

418
00:41:50,299 --> 00:41:51,675
By the way,

419
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:56,180
I did not expect that man
to deal with the pond spirit so easily.

420
00:41:58,140 --> 00:41:59,225
Indeed.

421
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:01,310
Even Gu-cheon found it strange.

422
00:42:01,393 --> 00:42:04,688
He asked if it was truly the pond spirit
that killed the princes.

423
00:42:07,066 --> 00:42:08,025
Father.

424
00:42:09,902 --> 00:42:14,657
How did the Crown Prince,
the first son of the late King, pass away?

425
00:42:19,662 --> 00:42:22,206
- Your Highness!
- What is going on?

426
00:42:22,706 --> 00:42:23,624
Your Highness!

427
00:42:38,305 --> 00:42:39,431
A curse.

428
00:42:43,936 --> 00:42:46,522
He was killed by the curse of a spirit.

429
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:49,942
And the second son of the late King?

430
00:43:08,377 --> 00:43:10,004
<i>A spirit killed him.</i>

431
00:43:10,879 --> 00:43:13,882
The third and fourth brothers as well.
All of them.

432
00:43:18,596 --> 00:43:23,684
<i>Are you sure those princes were killed</i>
<i>by the pond spirit?</i>

433
00:43:29,565 --> 00:43:31,025
What is the matter?

434
00:43:35,237 --> 00:43:38,824
Your Majesty.
Preparations for the hunt are complete.

435
00:43:38,907 --> 00:43:40,909
Prince Yeongan is waiting.

436
00:43:41,493 --> 00:43:42,536
Very well.

437
00:43:47,916 --> 00:43:49,501
We will talk again later.

438
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:44,348
<i>- He can never know about the pond spirit.</i>
- <i>Stop. I do not wish to hear it.</i>

439
00:44:44,431 --> 00:44:46,725
<i>- You need not know.</i>
<i>- I do not wish to know.</i>

440
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:48,435
<i>I will wipe out every last seed!</i>

441
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:49,520
<i>Please, someone.</i>

442
00:44:49,603 --> 00:44:50,979
<i>Admitted to the crime.</i>

443
00:44:51,063 --> 00:44:51,897
<i>Help me.</i>

444
00:44:51,980 --> 00:44:54,775
<i>Do not say</i>
<i>that my own child hears such things.</i>

445
00:44:54,858 --> 00:44:56,193
<i>It is your father who is the</i>…

446
00:44:59,279 --> 00:45:00,114
Why cry again?

447
00:45:01,198 --> 00:45:03,033
More importantly, why are you still here?

448
00:45:03,117 --> 00:45:04,910
There was something I missed.

449
00:45:05,536 --> 00:45:07,746
The one who cursed Prince Yeongan.

450
00:45:07,830 --> 00:45:09,665
It was not
the Most Favored Lady of the Court.

451
00:45:11,291 --> 00:45:14,670
The spirit that clawed at your soul
was not her.

452
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:16,296
Then…

453
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:20,217
who was the spirit that tried to kill

454
00:45:21,009 --> 00:45:22,553
Prince Yeongan?

455
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:38,527
I will take my revenge.

456
00:45:40,028 --> 00:45:41,071
The King

457
00:45:42,614 --> 00:45:46,118
must pay for his sins.

458
00:45:49,288 --> 00:45:52,291
The secret of the royal family…

459
00:45:52,791 --> 00:45:53,709
I will…

460
00:45:54,793 --> 00:45:58,297
I will become the real one.

461
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:03,802
I will eradicate the royal bloodline!

462
00:47:24,299 --> 00:47:27,302
Prince Yeongan.
We must go to Prince Yeongan!

463
00:47:29,179 --> 00:47:30,305
It is already too late.

464
00:47:40,023 --> 00:47:41,191
Your Highness!

465
00:47:41,275 --> 00:47:42,818
Halt!

466
00:47:44,444 --> 00:47:46,655
Your Highness!

467
00:47:56,915 --> 00:47:58,333
Attend to His Highness at once!

468
00:47:58,834 --> 00:48:01,628
- Your Highness!
- Summon the royal physician!

469
00:48:03,589 --> 00:48:05,424
Then you must leave the palace at once.

470
00:48:05,507 --> 00:48:06,633
Run now.

471
00:48:06,717 --> 00:48:08,719
Since you failed to save Prince Yeongan,

472
00:48:09,303 --> 00:48:11,471
His Majesty will kill you.

473
00:48:12,055 --> 00:48:13,223
If I leave now,

474
00:48:14,474 --> 00:48:16,768
you will die as Prince Yeongan did.

475
00:48:20,731 --> 00:48:22,149
It does not concern you.

476
00:48:22,232 --> 00:48:23,191
Yes, it does.

477
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:25,277
You saved me.

478
00:48:25,861 --> 00:48:28,697
You risked your life
to cross into the Realm of Gwi for me.

479
00:48:28,780 --> 00:48:31,366
And this time, I will save you.

480
00:51:31,463 --> 00:51:34,758
Subtitle translation by: Yun-hee Jang
